1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,627
<i>Just kill me instead.</i>

2
00:00:02,711 --> 00:00:04,212
<i>Let my family go.</i>

3
00:00:04,295 --> 00:00:06,840
[EMIL] <i>None of you deserve to live!</i>

4
00:00:06,923 --> 00:00:08,091
<i>- Enough, please!</i>
<i>- Magnus!</i>

5
00:00:08,174 --> 00:00:09,718
<i>Stop! Don't!</i>

6
00:00:09,801 --> 00:00:12,011
<i>Don't! </i>[GROANS IN PAIN]

7
00:00:13,138 --> 00:00:14,764
- [LIAM GRUNTS]
- [EMIL GROANS IN PAIN]

8
00:00:15,598 --> 00:00:18,810
[BOTH GRUNTING]

9
00:00:20,353 --> 00:00:21,479
[SHOUTS FURIOUSLY]

10
00:00:21,563 --> 00:00:22,939
- [GUNSHOT]
- [GROANS]

11
00:00:23,022 --> 00:00:24,441
[MAGNUS]<i> Greta.</i>

12
00:00:24,524 --> 00:00:26,526
[SOBS] <i>I'll call for help.</i>

13
00:00:27,944 --> 00:00:29,529
[MAGNUS] <i>I'm sorry.</i>

14
00:00:31,281 --> 00:00:32,407
[SNIFFLING]

15
00:00:32,991 --> 00:00:35,410
[EMIL, TEARFULLY]
<i>You've done nothing wrong, Ayen.</i>

16
00:00:35,493 --> 00:00:38,038
<i>Magnus used you.</i>

17
00:00:38,121 --> 00:00:40,665
<i>Greta murdered you.</i>

18
00:00:41,499 --> 00:00:44,294
<i>I couldn't protect you. </i>[SOBS]

19
00:00:44,377 --> 00:00:48,798
<i>I won't give up. I'll continue my revenge!</i>

20
00:00:48,882 --> 00:00:52,051
<i>Liam, enough. I'm begging you.</i>
<i>I'm sorry, I'm sorry.</i>

21
00:00:52,135 --> 00:00:54,220
<i>I didn't expect it to go this far.</i>

22
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:56,473
<i>- Come with me.</i>
<i>- No, I'll talk to him!</i>

23
00:00:56,556 --> 00:00:58,475
[EMIL GRUNTS]

24
00:01:00,101 --> 00:01:05,273
[SOBS BROKENLY] <i>Leni! Leni!</i>

25
00:01:06,816 --> 00:01:08,818
<i>- Wendy!</i>
- [WENDY WHIMPERS]

26
00:01:08,902 --> 00:01:11,029
<i>The truth is, you don't owe me anything.</i>

27
00:01:11,112 --> 00:01:12,530
<i>But your mother does!</i>

28
00:01:12,614 --> 00:01:15,742
[BOTH GRUNTING]

29
00:01:15,825 --> 00:01:20,330
- [BLOWS LANDING]
- [BOTH GRUNTING]

30
00:01:24,667 --> 00:01:26,961
- [GUNSHOT ECHOING]
- [HOMER GROANS]

31
00:01:27,045 --> 00:01:29,088
[SCREAMS IN PAIN]

32
00:01:29,714 --> 00:01:30,632
[HOMER] <i>Go ahead!</i>

33
00:01:30,715 --> 00:01:32,050
<i>Shoot me dead!</i>

34
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:33,259
[OLSEN] <i>I won't do that.</i>

35
00:01:33,343 --> 00:01:34,594
<i>I may be your son,</i>

36
00:01:34,677 --> 00:01:36,221
<i>but we are not the same!</i>

37
00:01:48,817 --> 00:01:53,988
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

38
00:01:57,742 --> 00:02:00,286
[BAGS THUD]

39
00:02:01,746 --> 00:02:07,502
[PLANTS RUSTLING]

40
00:02:31,442 --> 00:02:38,366
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

41
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:10,398
Liam!

42
00:03:11,566 --> 00:03:12,525
Dude!

43
00:03:12,609 --> 00:03:19,616
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

44
00:03:22,911 --> 00:03:23,870
Liam!

45
00:03:27,165 --> 00:03:28,207
Bro!

46
00:03:29,834 --> 00:03:31,169
Liam! Liam…

47
00:03:32,337 --> 00:03:33,546
Bro!

48
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:36,299
Papa got shot! He needs help!

49
00:03:37,258 --> 00:03:38,218
Your mom?

50
00:03:46,267 --> 00:03:48,102
[VOICE PROMPT]
<i>The subscriber cannot be reached.</i>

51
00:03:48,186 --> 00:03:49,896
<i>- Please try again later.</i>
- [FIN] We're almost there.

52
00:03:49,979 --> 00:03:50,813
[MACKY] Let's go.

53
00:03:51,439 --> 00:03:52,857
Fin, were you able to reach Olsen?

54
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:54,651
- Not so far.
- You still can't?

55
00:03:54,734 --> 00:03:56,361
[VOICE PROMPT] <i>The subscriber</i>
<i>cannot be reached.</i>

56
00:03:56,444 --> 00:03:57,445
But we're near.

57
00:03:57,528 --> 00:03:59,072
See? There it is.

58
00:03:59,822 --> 00:04:01,115
- It's right there!
- We're here.

59
00:04:02,659 --> 00:04:06,955
[EMIL GASPING, GRUNTING]

60
00:04:09,165 --> 00:04:10,208
Mama's gone.

61
00:04:12,335 --> 00:04:13,878
Emil killed her.

62
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:16,214
[GROANS]

63
00:04:16,297 --> 00:04:20,051
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

64
00:04:20,635 --> 00:04:21,719
And Emil?

65
00:04:23,638 --> 00:04:25,056
I don't know.

66
00:04:25,139 --> 00:04:32,021
[EMIL BREATHING LABORIOUSLY]

67
00:04:35,566 --> 00:04:39,445
[EMIL BREATHING LABORIOUSLY]

68
00:04:40,989 --> 00:04:41,948
[GROANS]

69
00:04:42,031 --> 00:04:45,326
[BREATHING LABORIOUSLY]

70
00:04:46,577 --> 00:04:47,745
[SHARP GRUNT]

71
00:04:49,622 --> 00:04:51,582
- [GUN COCKS]
- [OLSEN] Liam, get down!

72
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:53,084
[GUNSHOTS]

73
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:54,252
[PAINED GRUNT]

74
00:04:54,836 --> 00:04:55,878
[GUNSHOTS]

75
00:04:55,962 --> 00:05:01,426
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

76
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:03,386
Liam Roja!

77
00:05:04,220 --> 00:05:05,555
Get out here!

78
00:05:07,515 --> 00:05:10,059
You took everything from me!

79
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:13,354
Let's finish this once and for all!

80
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:16,399
Show yourself!

81
00:05:16,482 --> 00:05:21,612
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

82
00:05:21,696 --> 00:05:24,407
Let's end this!

83
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:26,075
- [EMIL SHOUTS FURIOUSLY]
- [RITA SCREAMS]

84
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:27,201
[TIRES SCREECHING]

85
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:28,911
[BODY THUDS]

86
00:05:31,122 --> 00:05:38,087
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

87
00:05:40,882 --> 00:05:42,133
[OLSEN] Macky!

88
00:05:46,888 --> 00:05:48,347
[CAR DOORS SHUT]

89
00:05:48,431 --> 00:05:54,729
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

90
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:04,697
Papa was shot. Doc, help him!

91
00:06:04,781 --> 00:06:06,365
- Where is he?
- [LIAM] Over there. Let's go!

92
00:06:14,248 --> 00:06:19,670
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

93
00:06:33,976 --> 00:06:34,894
[EMIL GRUNTS]

94
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:40,566
[GROANS]

95
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:45,863
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

96
00:06:45,947 --> 00:06:49,951
[GUNSHOTS]

97
00:06:50,034 --> 00:06:56,374
["ROJA" THEME SONG PLAYING]

98
00:07:12,056 --> 00:07:17,520
[SONG CONTINUES]

99
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:29,031
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

100
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:34,620
[GUNSHOT]

101
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:35,872
[GUNSHOTS]

102
00:07:36,873 --> 00:07:38,833
[FURIOUS SHOUT]

103
00:07:41,627 --> 00:07:42,795
[AX SWISHING]

104
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:44,005
[FLESH SQUELCHES]

105
00:07:45,173 --> 00:07:46,090
[GROANS]

106
00:07:47,508 --> 00:07:54,265
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING
UNDER THEME SONG]

107
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:08,821
[DRAMATIC MUSIC FADES
INTO POIGNANT MUSIC]

108
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:10,406
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

109
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,996
Mama taught me right from wrong.

110
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:20,875
That's why it's difficult
to accept all this.

111
00:08:25,213 --> 00:08:26,506
She hurt a lot of people.

112
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:31,427
A lot of people got put in danger.

113
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:32,970
A lot of lives were lost.

114
00:08:35,473 --> 00:08:37,183
All because of her decisions.

115
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:41,896
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

116
00:08:47,735 --> 00:08:51,113
I know Mama believes she did
everything because of love.

117
00:08:53,324 --> 00:08:55,284
Love for her family.

118
00:08:56,077 --> 00:08:57,036
For us.

119
00:09:00,665 --> 00:09:01,707
For me.

120
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:04,460
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

121
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:07,088
But there are times when love,

122
00:09:09,048 --> 00:09:11,384
when it's not guided by conscience,

123
00:09:12,468 --> 00:09:14,178
leads to destruction.

124
00:09:15,805 --> 00:09:18,474
The line between right and wrong
becomes blurred.

125
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:24,647
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

126
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:26,941
No life is more important than another.

127
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:30,820
And it's not right to sacrifice
the lives of others

128
00:09:30,903 --> 00:09:32,530
for your own family's sake.

129
00:09:33,823 --> 00:09:36,492
At the end of the day,
I think Mama realized that.

130
00:09:37,493 --> 00:09:38,828
She understood that.

131
00:09:39,787 --> 00:09:41,914
She regretted everything she had done.

132
00:09:42,540 --> 00:09:44,584
She regretted all of her decisions.

133
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:48,754
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

134
00:09:48,838 --> 00:09:50,214
And in the end,

135
00:09:51,340 --> 00:09:53,634
Mama sacrificed her life…

136
00:09:56,178 --> 00:09:57,972
to save me.

137
00:09:58,055 --> 00:10:02,435
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

138
00:10:02,518 --> 00:10:04,353
For the family she loved.

139
00:10:08,524 --> 00:10:11,444
I know it's hard to erase
the anger in your hearts.

140
00:10:14,113 --> 00:10:16,198
I try to suppress it too, every day.

141
00:10:17,408 --> 00:10:20,494
But if there's one thing
I learned from all of this, it's this.

142
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:23,289
Hate

143
00:10:24,582 --> 00:10:26,334
and thirst for revenge

144
00:10:27,251 --> 00:10:29,962
will only bring unimaginable destruction.

145
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,882
[LIAM BREATHES DEEPLY]

146
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:34,842
It is only love

147
00:10:35,343 --> 00:10:37,011
and forgiveness

148
00:10:37,678 --> 00:10:39,096
that can save us.

149
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:41,766
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

150
00:10:41,849 --> 00:10:45,811
I know she's not here right now,

151
00:10:47,229 --> 00:10:49,523
so I'm going to say this myself.

152
00:10:52,026 --> 00:10:53,194
[STIFLED SOB]

153
00:10:54,111 --> 00:10:56,155
I ask all of you for forgiveness.

154
00:10:56,238 --> 00:11:02,495
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

155
00:11:04,205 --> 00:11:06,165
For all that has happened to you…

156
00:11:06,248 --> 00:11:10,961
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

157
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:13,005
For all of the lives lost…

158
00:11:14,548 --> 00:11:15,633
I'm sorry.

159
00:11:15,716 --> 00:11:22,681
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

160
00:11:32,316 --> 00:11:35,444
I hope you can find it in your hearts
to forgive.

161
00:11:36,862 --> 00:11:43,702
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

162
00:11:58,759 --> 00:12:05,141
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

163
00:12:08,727 --> 00:12:10,104
[OLSEN] Ma! Here.

164
00:12:11,522 --> 00:12:14,775
Cheers? To a new beginning.

165
00:12:14,859 --> 00:12:18,112
Be careful, it's hot.
I even burned my tongue.

166
00:12:18,195 --> 00:12:19,405
[OLSEN CHUCKLES]

167
00:12:19,488 --> 00:12:20,823
[OLSEN SIGHS]

168
00:12:23,325 --> 00:12:25,578
A fresh start is hard as well.

169
00:12:27,037 --> 00:12:28,456
Especially if you're not here.

170
00:12:29,457 --> 00:12:32,042
You know, Ma, you're thinking
of whatever again.

171
00:12:33,294 --> 00:12:35,880
Whatever that is, we can do it.

172
00:12:35,963 --> 00:12:40,342
But it's true. We really have nothing.

173
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:43,721
Did someone offer you a job already?

174
00:12:44,513 --> 00:12:48,684
All the places I applied to
never replied back.

175
00:12:48,767 --> 00:12:52,354
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

176
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:53,689
Something will come.

177
00:12:55,524 --> 00:12:57,318
Just have faith. That's all…

178
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:01,238
That's all we can hope for.

179
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:04,909
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

180
00:13:04,992 --> 00:13:09,121
After surviving the hell we went through,

181
00:13:10,289 --> 00:13:14,335
now we're facing a new hell.

182
00:13:16,337 --> 00:13:17,421
You know, son?

183
00:13:18,714 --> 00:13:19,840
Sometimes…

184
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:23,719
Sometimes, it gets exhausting.

185
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:28,265
I'm fed up with this life.

186
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:30,976
Not everything is easy, right?

187
00:13:33,521 --> 00:13:34,563
But…

188
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:38,943
that's why we're getting a fresh start.

189
00:13:40,569 --> 00:13:41,987
And, hopefully,

190
00:13:42,071 --> 00:13:45,199
our new life will be so good
it makes up for…

191
00:13:47,826 --> 00:13:49,245
everything that happened to us.

192
00:13:49,328 --> 00:13:55,751
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

193
00:14:00,839 --> 00:14:06,971
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

194
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:09,890
[LIAM] This place

195
00:14:11,225 --> 00:14:12,601
was never meant to die.

196
00:14:14,103 --> 00:14:15,312
I want to reopen it.

197
00:14:16,397 --> 00:14:18,983
Resort. Restaurant.

198
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:21,235
Everything.

199
00:14:22,945 --> 00:14:26,156
But, dude, do you think
anyone will still go here?

200
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,534
After everything that happened here?

201
00:14:28,617 --> 00:14:30,119
You know, dude,

202
00:14:30,202 --> 00:14:31,620
La Playa Roja…

203
00:14:32,413 --> 00:14:33,789
It's not just a business.

204
00:14:34,957 --> 00:14:36,041
It's a legacy.

205
00:14:36,917 --> 00:14:38,377
It's my parents' legacy.

206
00:14:38,460 --> 00:14:41,130
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

207
00:14:41,213 --> 00:14:43,173
So I have to continue it.

208
00:14:43,841 --> 00:14:45,551
That was my promise to Papa.

209
00:14:47,303 --> 00:14:48,762
And I'm sure…

210
00:14:48,846 --> 00:14:52,141
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

211
00:14:52,224 --> 00:14:53,934
…that's what Mama would have wanted.

212
00:14:55,686 --> 00:14:56,729
Dude.

213
00:14:57,521 --> 00:14:58,981
If that's the case,

214
00:15:00,107 --> 00:15:01,483
I'll help you.

215
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:06,155
I promise you that I'll do
everything I can

216
00:15:06,238 --> 00:15:09,533
to make La Playa Roja become
the best resort restaurant

217
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:12,411
in the world!

218
00:15:13,746 --> 00:15:15,205
Of course you should.

219
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:19,835
- Thank you, okay?
- Thank you, Chef.

220
00:15:20,502 --> 00:15:22,338
You're welcome, Chef.

221
00:15:22,421 --> 00:15:23,631
[LUNA GIGGLES]

222
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,468
But wait,

223
00:15:28,093 --> 00:15:30,012
who's going to manage this place?

224
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:36,435
[HOPEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

225
00:15:39,271 --> 00:15:41,148
You should eat, Magnus.

226
00:15:42,858 --> 00:15:46,445
I'm sorry, this is all I brought.

227
00:15:49,865 --> 00:15:50,991
Wendy…

228
00:15:52,910 --> 00:15:54,620
Thank you for visiting.

229
00:15:54,703 --> 00:15:59,416
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

230
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:01,835
I know what you're going through.

231
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:05,130
You have to be strong.

232
00:16:06,048 --> 00:16:08,342
Don't get discouraged.

233
00:16:10,177 --> 00:16:12,221
You can get through this, Magnus.

234
00:16:13,305 --> 00:16:15,057
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

235
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:17,393
One day, you'll be released from here,

236
00:16:17,476 --> 00:16:19,603
and be with Liam.

237
00:16:22,523 --> 00:16:25,651
Well, that's all I'm holding on to.

238
00:16:27,444 --> 00:16:28,988
To be with my son.

239
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:32,408
How is he?

240
00:16:32,491 --> 00:16:34,451
You know, knowing Liam,

241
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:37,830
most likely, he's still grieving

242
00:16:39,039 --> 00:16:40,874
over Greta's death.

243
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:43,252
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

244
00:16:43,335 --> 00:16:45,379
He meets with Olsen.

245
00:16:47,381 --> 00:16:48,424
Wonderful.

246
00:16:49,925 --> 00:16:51,677
I'm happy they're friends again.

247
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:54,513
[MUSIC TURNS MELLOW]

248
00:16:54,596 --> 00:16:56,473
I'm sure Greta would have been happy

249
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:57,683
just the same.

250
00:17:00,394 --> 00:17:02,813
You know, it's actually true
what they say.

251
00:17:02,896 --> 00:17:05,983
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

252
00:17:06,066 --> 00:17:10,904
You only realize how important someone is
when you lose them.

253
00:17:14,366 --> 00:17:16,785
Greta's passing has made me realize

254
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:19,621
how much I truly loved her.

255
00:17:19,705 --> 00:17:23,625
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

256
00:17:24,251 --> 00:17:26,503
My only regret is…

257
00:17:29,006 --> 00:17:31,550
not being given the chance to…

258
00:17:33,761 --> 00:17:35,012
make up

259
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:39,266
for all the pain I caused her.

260
00:17:42,019 --> 00:17:43,312
Magnus,

261
00:17:45,189 --> 00:17:46,982
it's Liam you should make it up to.

262
00:17:49,318 --> 00:17:51,612
I was also like that.

263
00:17:52,529 --> 00:17:57,910
I made so many mistakes and have so many
shortcomings when it comes to my son.

264
00:17:57,993 --> 00:18:00,204
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

265
00:18:00,287 --> 00:18:01,705
But

266
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:04,750
I'll make it up to Olsen.

267
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:08,045
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

268
00:18:08,128 --> 00:18:11,215
And I won't let him suffer anymore.

269
00:18:11,298 --> 00:18:17,429
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

270
00:18:17,513 --> 00:18:18,639
You're right.

271
00:18:25,604 --> 00:18:26,814
[GLASS THUDS]

272
00:18:26,897 --> 00:18:28,232
Dude, this is on the house.

273
00:18:28,315 --> 00:18:30,526
- [PLATE THUDS]
- [CHAIR SCRAPING]

274
00:18:30,609 --> 00:18:31,735
Man!

275
00:18:32,778 --> 00:18:34,404
- [CHAIR THUDS]
- [GLASS CLINKS]

276
00:18:37,658 --> 00:18:40,661
I accept. I like the sound of it.

277
00:18:41,662 --> 00:18:45,374
"Olsen Bonifacio,
General Manager of La Playa Roja."

278
00:18:45,457 --> 00:18:46,875
It clicks. It clicks, dude.

279
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:48,919
I know this is what you really want to do.

280
00:18:49,002 --> 00:18:50,129
You still remember that?

281
00:18:50,838 --> 00:18:53,674
You even got mad at me
when I asked your dad to train me.

282
00:18:53,757 --> 00:18:56,260
- Let's forget that, man. That's over.
- [OLSEN CHUCKLES]

283
00:18:56,343 --> 00:18:57,302
I hope so.

284
00:18:59,179 --> 00:19:00,139
Dude.

285
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:02,141
Thank you.

286
00:19:03,392 --> 00:19:05,185
Papa said you also visit him.

287
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:09,439
Of course, dude. He's like family to me.

288
00:19:09,523 --> 00:19:10,440
Like you.

289
00:19:11,817 --> 00:19:13,819
- [PHONE RINGING]
- Sorry.

290
00:19:15,612 --> 00:19:16,446
[PHONE RINGING]

291
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:18,365
Mama keeps on calling me.

292
00:19:18,448 --> 00:19:20,993
She wants me to go with her somewhere.
I don't know where though.

293
00:19:21,076 --> 00:19:22,578
Go with her.

294
00:19:22,661 --> 00:19:24,413
- [PHONE RINGING]
- Go on.

295
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:26,248
Okay, dude.

296
00:19:28,083 --> 00:19:29,543
[LIAM CHUCKLES]

297
00:19:29,626 --> 00:19:31,044
I'll just change. Thanks again!

298
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:32,629
This had better taste good.

299
00:19:32,713 --> 00:19:34,756
Of course! Let's meet tomorrow.

300
00:19:38,218 --> 00:19:42,139
[REPORTER] <i>A few weeks after</i>
<i>the bloody incident at La Playa Roja,</i>

301
00:19:42,222 --> 00:19:46,393
<i>the ransom money has been returned</i>
<i>to the victims' families.</i>

302
00:19:46,476 --> 00:19:47,895
<i>But according to the report,</i>

303
00:19:47,978 --> 00:19:51,064
<i>they've yet to recover</i>
<i>jewelry worth millions</i>

304
00:19:51,148 --> 00:19:54,776
<i>that victim Ona Chan allegedly gave</i>
<i>to the hostage takers.</i>

305
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:58,739
<i>The police are still searching</i>
<i>for the missing jewelry,</i>

306
00:19:58,822 --> 00:20:01,992
<i>while investigating the whole incident.</i>

307
00:20:02,075 --> 00:20:08,957
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

308
00:20:14,004 --> 00:20:15,047
Yes, Ma?

309
00:20:15,130 --> 00:20:16,590
[WENDY] <i>Son, where are you?</i>

310
00:20:16,673 --> 00:20:18,383
<i>We're supposed to meet, right?</i>

311
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:20,677
Tell me where we're going first.

312
00:20:20,761 --> 00:20:22,763
To Magnus' rest house.

313
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:24,932
Sir Magnus' rest house?

314
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:27,809
But it's under investigation, Ma.

315
00:20:28,518 --> 00:20:30,103
We're going there?

316
00:20:30,187 --> 00:20:32,439
I just want to check something.

317
00:20:32,522 --> 00:20:34,066
Just what are you gonna check?

318
00:20:34,149 --> 00:20:35,984
Son, I'll tell you about it later.

319
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:38,695
Let's just go. Let's meet up.

320
00:20:38,779 --> 00:20:41,323
Okay, I'll go. Let's meet there.

321
00:20:41,406 --> 00:20:48,413
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

322
00:20:51,959 --> 00:20:55,587
[CABRAL SIGHS] It'll help your case
if you talk, Sebastian.

323
00:20:57,047 --> 00:20:59,675
How am I gonna talk when I know nothing?

324
00:21:00,467 --> 00:21:01,843
[SCOFFS]

325
00:21:02,344 --> 00:21:07,015
Just tell us where you hid the missing
jewelry that belonged to Ona Chan,

326
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:08,350
and the money.

327
00:21:08,433 --> 00:21:10,602
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

328
00:21:10,686 --> 00:21:11,645
Who knows?

329
00:21:12,729 --> 00:21:16,316
If you show that you are cooperating
with the investigation,

330
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:19,361
you may be forgiven by
the people you've wronged.

331
00:21:20,153 --> 00:21:22,864
Especially your son.

332
00:21:24,199 --> 00:21:26,535
I don't care about any of them anymore.

333
00:21:27,035 --> 00:21:28,370
[SCOFFS]

334
00:21:28,453 --> 00:21:32,040
Perhaps you have accomplices out there,
so you don't want to talk?

335
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:34,626
I already told you everything I know!

336
00:21:35,836 --> 00:21:37,004
[CABRAL] Sebastian.

337
00:21:37,087 --> 00:21:39,923
Just tell us who
your accomplices are already,

338
00:21:40,590 --> 00:21:44,219
as well as where you hid the jewelry
and the money.

339
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:46,054
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

340
00:21:46,138 --> 00:21:49,516
Why are you so interested
in the jewelry anyway?

341
00:21:49,599 --> 00:21:51,184
So you can get some for yourself?

342
00:21:51,268 --> 00:21:53,020
You'll look for it and steal--

343
00:21:53,103 --> 00:21:54,396
[BANGS ON TABLE]

344
00:21:54,479 --> 00:21:56,690
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

345
00:21:56,773 --> 00:21:59,026
Don't lump me in with the likes of you!

346
00:21:59,109 --> 00:22:00,360
Huh?!

347
00:22:01,069 --> 00:22:03,447
If you're gonna be stubborn,

348
00:22:03,530 --> 00:22:05,198
I won't be able to help you!

349
00:22:05,866 --> 00:22:07,326
I'll say it again.

350
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:09,328
I don't know anything!

351
00:22:11,204 --> 00:22:12,748
- [GRUNTS]
- [THUDS]

352
00:22:12,831 --> 00:22:18,462
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

353
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:27,679
[SUSPENSEFUL STING]

354
00:22:28,930 --> 00:22:30,599
- Bro, have you heard?
- What?

355
00:22:30,682 --> 00:22:32,684
Some of the ransom is still missing

356
00:22:32,768 --> 00:22:35,187
from the hostage-taking incident
at La Playa Roja.

357
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:37,481
- Really?
- They said it's mostly jewelry.

358
00:22:37,564 --> 00:22:39,816
- Yeah?
- Worth a fortune!

359
00:22:40,358 --> 00:22:41,651
Where is it hidden?

360
00:22:41,735 --> 00:22:42,819
Nobody knows.

361
00:22:43,612 --> 00:22:45,947
[GUARD 2] Those hostage takers are clever.

362
00:22:46,823 --> 00:22:50,285
If they can't benefit from it,
then no one will.

363
00:22:50,368 --> 00:22:54,372
I'm guessing that Homer Sebastian
knows where it's hidden.

364
00:22:54,456 --> 00:22:56,374
He's just not fessing up.

365
00:22:56,458 --> 00:22:59,503
But once he gets out of here,

366
00:22:59,586 --> 00:23:02,923
I bet he'll go back and get all of it.

367
00:23:03,006 --> 00:23:05,092
- It's gonna be a feast for him!
- [SCOFFS]

368
00:23:05,175 --> 00:23:06,968
That's if he can get out from jail.

369
00:23:07,052 --> 00:23:09,096
With how heavy
the charges against him are,

370
00:23:09,179 --> 00:23:10,889
he'll probably die in here.

371
00:23:10,972 --> 00:23:12,099
[GUARD 1] You have a point.

372
00:23:12,182 --> 00:23:15,352
It's gonna take him an entire lifetime
before he can leave.

373
00:23:15,435 --> 00:23:18,897
[SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING]

374
00:23:18,980 --> 00:23:21,733
[VAN DOOR SLIDES OPEN, THUDS]

375
00:23:36,414 --> 00:23:42,587
[SINISTER MUSIC CONTINUES]

376
00:23:45,257 --> 00:23:48,135
<i>The jewelry you're hiding</i>
<i>is worth millions.</i>

377
00:23:48,218 --> 00:23:51,346
<i>Find an island</i>
<i>and take some hostages.</i>

378
00:23:52,556 --> 00:23:54,307
[OLSEN] <i>What are we doing here?</i>

379
00:23:54,391 --> 00:23:56,810
<i>The police just won't leave</i>
<i>this place alone.</i>

380
00:23:56,893 --> 00:23:58,979
<i>I hope they don't come today.</i>

381
00:23:59,062 --> 00:24:01,481
<i>Money and material possessions</i>
<i>are not the answer.</i>

382
00:24:02,065 --> 00:24:05,110
<i>You risked your life for them</i>
<i>countless times!</i>

383
00:24:05,193 --> 00:24:07,237
<i>And then what?</i>
<i>We're still going to suffer?!</i>

384
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:09,948
<i>The decision is yours, Aunt Wendy.</i>
<i>What choice will you make?</i>

385
00:24:13,952 --> 00:24:19,416
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
